External Tables

*External tables allow you to create tables on data stored external to Snowflake
1.Definition in Snowflake metadata
2.Data in external location

• External table functionality lets you query an external table like a regular table Join with other tables

• Create views on top of external tables

• External tables are read-only since they point to external storage. 。 DML operations cannot be performed on them.

• External table data does not contribute to Snowflake storage costs
  the compute cost is charged when queries are executed
